13. Hepatic dysfunction defined as:
 Total bilirubin  1.5 × ULN unless the participant has documented Gilbert's syndrome (in this case total bilirubin ≥3 × ULN);

 AST and ALT  3 × ULN;

 Alkaline phosphatase  2.5 × ULN or  5 × ULN if liver metastases present (unless the participant has bone metastasis only, in which case the alkaline phosphatase value will not be considered as exclusion criteria);

 aPTT  1.25 × ULN and INR  1.25 unless the participant is receiving anticoagulation, then aPTT and INR should be within the therapeutic range of the intended use;

 Albumin  30 g/L.
